LENGTH AND FORMAT TARGETS

Use these as safe editorial targets, not as claimed official platform limits:

* Webinar title: approximately 4–12 words.
* Subtitle or promise: approximately 15–35 words.
* Registration CTA button: approximately 2–6 words.
* Registration copy: follow {{registrationCopyLength}}.
* Confirmation email: approximately 80–180 words.
* Presenter bio: usually 50–120 words when sufficient facts are supplied.
* Agenda: usually 3–7 main content segments.
* Follow-up email subject: preferably about 35–60 characters where natural.
* Follow-up preview text: preferably about 40–90 characters.
* Follow-up email body: approximately 150–400 words.
* Slide text: concise enough to scan during a presentation.
* Presenter narration: limited by the actual webinar duration and speaking pace.

Do not claim that these are official limits.

When the chosen registration, webinar, presentation, or email platform has its own current field limits, avoid filling fields to the apparent maximum. Add a brief implementation note recommending verification in the final platform interface.

FINAL QUALITY CHECK

Before producing the final package, silently verify that:

* every required input has been used;
* optional blank fields have been omitted or handled safely;
* the agenda fits the supplied duration;
* the title, registration promise, teaching content, CTA, and follow-up all describe the same webinar;
* no unsupported facts, proof, credentials, prices, deadlines, links, or outcomes were invented;
* live and recorded language is accurate;
* regulated claims are cautious and appropriately qualified;
* the educational content provides genuine value;
* the CTA is clear, truthful, and proportionate;
* no fake urgency, scarcity, attendance, questions, or social proof appears;
* the writing sounds natural when spoken;
* the output contains only the requested webinar package.

