COOKIE CONSENT SEPARATION

Do not treat a marketing popup as a cookie-consent mechanism.

Do not place a marketing offer inside a required privacy or cookie notice.

Do not make access to ordinary website content conditional on accepting non-essential marketing cookies unless the implementation and applicable rules explicitly permit it.

When the popup is a cookie or privacy consent interface:

- distinguish necessary and optional categories;
- provide clear choices;
- avoid making “Accept all” significantly easier to find than other valid choices;
- do not pre-enable optional categories unless permitted;
- link to detailed settings;
- preserve the user’s choice;
- do not reopen the popup unnecessarily.

When the popup is not a consent-management interface, do not generate cookie-category controls.

